newsitem.title: USA: US spot prods ease with NYMEX in pre-holiday trade.
newsitem.headline: US spot prods ease with NYMEX in pre-holiday trade.

text.p: U.S. spot products stayed lower in late afternoon dealings on Friday tracking a profit-taking slump on NYMEX, industry sources said.
Despite the prices drop of about 0.75 cent a gallon, dealings were extremely quiet as players began thier weekend early. Differentials were stable and completed deals were few.
NYMEX will be closed on Monday in observance of the U.S. Labor Day holiday.
New York Habor conventional M2-grade gasoline was pegged at 2.50 cents under the print of the September NYMEX contract, which expired at the close.
Gulf Coast M1 conventional unleaded was also stable, with offers at 4.25 cents under, brokers said.
-- Franklin Paul, New York Energy Desk +1 212 859 1620
